Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.58,0:00:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to this month’s broadcast. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.62,0:00:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Here are just a few highlights \Nof what we will enjoy: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.46,0:00:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Has anyone ever angrily confronted \Nyou about your beliefs \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.79,0:00:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and you found yourself \Nstruggling to respond? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.13,0:00:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You are not alone. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.23,0:00:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In this dramatization, we will learn \Nhow Grayson faces this same challenge.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.31,0:00:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,With the right circumstances, \Nsome have enjoyed full-time service \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.71,0:00:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,while successfully raising a family. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.28,0:00:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What did they do to make that possible? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.95,0:00:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The Schiller’s life story \Nwill help answer that question. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.45,0:00:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We will see the excitement and benefits \Nthat come from attending pioneer school. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.19,0:00:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But these students are not pioneers; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.23,0:00:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,they are all in Bethel service. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.06,0:00:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And we will learn ways \Nto manage our time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.60,0:00:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we can do \N“the more important things.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.33,0:00:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All this and more \Non this edition of JW Broadcasting!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.29,0:01:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Many have found public witnessing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.53,0:01:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to be an incredibly productive way \Nto share the good news in their territory. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.76,0:01:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Often, when we think \Nof this kind of ministry, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.27,0:01:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,we might imagine being on a busy street \Nor in some other urban area. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.07,0:01:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s see what it’s like \Nwhen public witnessing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.57,0:01:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is done in a very different location.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.54,0:01:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,In the book of Romans, \Nthe first chapter, verse 20, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.75,0:01:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,it talks about how you \Ncan perceive Jehovah’s creative power \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.42,0:01:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,by what we see in creation around us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.65,0:01:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,When you’re in a national park \Nand you see the beauty of these parks, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.26,0:01:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you immediately think of that scripture.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.96,0:01:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We have individuals driving \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.96,0:01:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,from an hour and a half \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.96,0:01:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to over three hours one-way \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.57,0:01:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to share in this form of witnessing.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.44,0:02:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,National parks generally have \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.44,0:02:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,what is called a freeness of speech area. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.81,0:02:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So that allows us \Nto be able to get permission \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.44,0:02:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to go into the parks \Nto set up our carts there. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.28,0:02:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s just a nice place to come and relax, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.82,0:02:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and when people are relaxed, \Nthey’re wanting to talk.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.59,0:02:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,They already kind of have \Na sense of closeness with God; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.09,0:02:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,it kind of gets them thinking \Nabout their spirituality, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.26,0:02:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and then when they see our cart \Ndisplayed so nicely about that, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.76,0:02:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,it kind of draws them toward that.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.16,0:02:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You will find visitors \Nfrom all parts of the world. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.07,0:02:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Many cultures are represented.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.14,0:02:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And quite often, \Nwe will have literature in their language. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.28,0:02:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,There are many that benefit \Nfrom our work at the carts. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.28,0:02:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But especially noteworthy are those \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.45,0:02:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,who do not have access to Bible literature. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.49,0:02:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,A Chinese couple came up, and they said, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.82,0:02:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“Thank you for giving us \Nthe Bible in our language.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.06,0:02:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That made our day. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.73,0:03:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It was fabulous!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.46,0:03:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,They may not stop. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.80,0:03:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,They may not talk to us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.80,0:03:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But they see it, \Nand that registers in their mind\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.87,0:03:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,—that they’ve seen this \Nat an airport or in their city. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.80,0:03:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And now they’re going to look into it \Nor go to the website and wonder: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.67,0:03:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,‘What was that all about? \NWhat were those people doing there?’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.34,0:03:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We sit here sometimes \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.15,0:03:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking we need to pinch ourselves \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.15,0:03:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,because it’s so beautiful \Nthat we’ve been given the privilege \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.68,0:03:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,of doing the cart work \Nin a location like this.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.05,0:03:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Very soon, \Nthese national parks will not just be \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.22,0:03:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,isolated places that we have to travel to\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.59,0:03:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—the entire world will be that national park. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.03,0:03:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And what a joy it will be \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.43,0:03:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,when every single person alive \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.77,0:03:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,can enjoy that beautiful painting \Nthat our Creator has made for us! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.81,0:03:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s qualities \Ncan certainly be perceived \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.58,0:03:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,just by taking \Nthe time to study creation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.18,0:03:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can see the power \Nof giving a witness in a beautiful location \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.62,0:03:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that naturally draws attention \Nto what Jehovah has made. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.39,0:04:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, \Npermission from park authorities \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.72,0:04:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is often needed in advance, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.96,0:04:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,but this idea of buying out \Ntime to appreciate something \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.53,0:04:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,takes us nicely \Ninto our discussion for this month.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.07,0:04:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like to talk about a valuable asset \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.70,0:04:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that every one of us possesses \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.71,0:04:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,—time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.71,0:04:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It certainly is something \Nthat is on our minds \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.88,0:04:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,as we go about our day’s activities. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.21,0:04:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Just think of how often \Nyou look at a clock, your watch, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.02,0:04:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,or your cell phone to check the time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.79,0:04:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do we do that? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.79,0:04:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably to see \Nif we are ahead of time, on time, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.09,0:04:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,behind time, or out of time!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.86,0:04:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But what exactly is time? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.90,0:04:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,One dictionary says \Nit is “a nonspatial continuum.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.90,0:04:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Another says \Nit is “the thing that is measured \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.60,0:04:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,as seconds, minutes, \Nhours, days, and years.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.41,0:04:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,To explain exactly what time is \Nin simple terms is nearly impossible, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.41,0:05:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Bible does not define it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.12,0:05:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,which may suggest that Jehovah knows \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.49,0:05:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,it is beyond our ability to understand fully.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.16,0:05:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But the Bible does discuss time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.33,0:05:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It shows that Jehovah is very time conscious. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.73,0:05:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It speaks of time \Nas something that we should use wisely. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.53,0:05:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And it gives us \Nthe amazing hope of living into infinity\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.67,0:05:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,—that is, endless time.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.61,0:05:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We do know this about time: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.94,0:05:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Every human has exactly the same number \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.75,0:05:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,of hours and minutes in each day. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.18,0:05:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Rich people cannot buy more hours, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.68,0:05:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and scientists cannot invent new minutes. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.89,0:05:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We can never recoup \Nthe time we have wasted; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.29,0:05:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,neither can we save it \Nto spend on another day. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.93,0:05:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Just think, we have exactly \Nthe same number of hours \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.87,0:05:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,to use each day that Jesus Christ \Nhad when he was on the earth! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.90,0:05:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And we can be sure \Nthat no human used his time more wisely \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.61,0:06:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,than did God’s Son. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.21,0:06:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It has been said that time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.21,0:06:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,is the most valuable thing \Na human can spend. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.55,0:06:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And so it is up to us \Nhow we will use the time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.02,0:06:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that is at our disposal. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.62,0:06:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,In this regard, there is a Bible principle \Nthat gives us good direction, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.49,0:06:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,a principle that was shared \Nwith us by the apostle Paul \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.86,0:06:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,at Philippians 1:9, 10. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.03,0:06:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,He wrote in verse 9: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.27,0:06:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“And this is what I continue praying,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.44,0:06:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and in verse 10, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.47,0:06:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“that you may make sure \Nof the more important things.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.51,0:06:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the theme of this month’s program \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.85,0:06:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is “Make Time for \N‘the More Important Things.’”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.15,0:06:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,This presents us with a two-fold challenge. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.75,0:06:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we have to determine \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.42,0:06:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,what are the more important things of life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.03,0:06:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,In the scripture we just read, \Nsome Bible translations say \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.90,0:06:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,“have a sense of what is vital.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.90,0:07:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So we must distinguish \Nbetween activities that are merely trivial \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.11,0:07:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and those that really matter.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.31,0:07:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition to the obligation \Nto work to support one’s family, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.71,0:07:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to care for necessary household chores, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.62,0:07:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and to look after one’s children \Nor aging parents, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.95,0:07:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,we have many important things \Nof a spiritual nature \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.96,0:07:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that deserve our full attention: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.26,0:07:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,reading and meditating on God’s Word, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.26,0:07:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,studying the Bible personally \Nand in family worship, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.60,0:07:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,preparing for and attending \Ncongregation meetings, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.27,0:07:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,caring for any responsibilities \Nthat we have in the congregation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.14,0:07:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and participating in the Christian ministry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.38,0:07:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides all of that, \Nwho does not want some time to rest, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.88,0:07:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,to exercise, to work in the garden, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.95,0:07:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,to enjoy some recreation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.09,0:07:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,or to visit with family and friends?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.76,0:07:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever felt that you did not have \Nenough time to do all those things\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.73,0:08:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,—that you have difficulty \Nfitting all the spiritual activities \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.43,0:08:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,into your busy life? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.93,0:08:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,As much as we might like to, \Nwe cannot add an extra hour to our day \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.87,0:08:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,or another day to our week \Nto accomplish more things. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.94,0:08:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have to be selective \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.91,0:08:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,about how we spend \Nthe time that we have.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.75,0:08:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We will get the most accomplished \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.82,0:08:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,if we prioritize \Nthe things that really matter. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.32,0:08:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And what does that mean? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.53,0:08:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,To prioritize means to decide \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.53,0:08:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,which tasks are more important \Nand to do them first. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.37,0:08:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, \Ndecide what must be given attention \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.87,0:08:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,prior to other things.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.31,0:08:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a Bible proverb \Nthat nicely illustrates \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.24,0:08:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the importance \Nof prioritizing life’s activities. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.71,0:08:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Proverbs 12:11 states: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.95,0:08:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“The one who cultivates his land \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.82,0:08:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,“will be satisfied with food, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.09,0:09:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,“but the one pursuing worthless things \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.62,0:09:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is lacking good sense.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.46,0:09:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What a clear warning that is for a farmer \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.26,0:09:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,not to fill up his day \Nwith worthless endeavors \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.37,0:09:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and waste the precious time that he \Nshould be spending working in his field!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.17,0:09:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Likewise, a Christian \Nwho diligently cultivates his spirituality \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.68,0:09:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,can be confident of Jehovah’s blessing, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.68,0:09:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,whereas a person \Nwho is distracted by worthless activities \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.52,0:09:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,puts his relationship with God in danger. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.02,0:09:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we avoid that? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.52,0:09:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,By not taking valuable time \Naway from spiritual pursuits \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.99,0:09:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to spend on the things that distract us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.40,0:09:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,from serving Jehovah whole-souled.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.07,0:09:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, when it comes \Nto communicating with others, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.44,0:09:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,what should take priority? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.77,0:09:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Starting our day \Nby giving Jehovah praise and thanks \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.54,0:09:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,in prayer for another day of life \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.95,0:09:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,or telephoning an old friend to catch up \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.35,0:10:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,on the latest news in his or her life? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.18,0:10:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s nothing wrong \Nwith talking to a friend. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.25,0:10:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But we need to make sure we take the time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.46,0:10:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to talk to our very best Friend, Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.69,0:10:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously, it is more important \Nto communicate with our heavenly Father, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.00,0:10:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so praying to him should be a priority.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.74,0:10:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The apostle Paul had more \Nto say about time management. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.91,0:10:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,At Ephesians 5:15-17, he wrote: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.44,0:10:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“So keep strict watch that how you walk \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.78,0:10:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,“is not as unwise but as wise persons, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.62,0:10:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,“making the best use of your time, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.22,0:10:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“because the days are wicked. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.76,0:10:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“On this account stop being unreasonable, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.63,0:10:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“but keep perceiving what \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.63,0:10:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the will of Jehovah is.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.56,0:10:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we can address \Nthe second part of our challenge: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.53,0:10:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to make ample time to care \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.10,0:10:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,for the more important things of life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.91,0:10:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What does Paul’s counsel \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.94,0:11:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to ‘make the best use of your time’ \Nactually mean? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.41,0:11:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Literally, in Greek, \Nit means to ‘buy out the appointed time.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.42,0:11:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That implies buying time \Nat the expense of something else. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.42,0:11:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So it helps to analyze \Nhow our time is actually being spent \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.69,0:11:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and to see what adjustments are needed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.50,0:11:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we can buy out, or make, \Ntime for the more important things.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.80,0:11:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If we ‘perceive what the will of Jehovah is,’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.67,0:11:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,then we certainly will want \Nto use as much time as possible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.64,0:11:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to forge an ever stronger \Nrelationship with him \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.81,0:11:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and to share fully in sacred service. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.45,0:11:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have definite periods set aside \Nfor the spiritual activities of life?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.32,0:11:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,For congregation meetings, \Nthe schedule is set for us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.66,0:11:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We know exactly when \Nour congregation meets \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.66,0:11:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,for its midweek \Nand weekend meetings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.93,0:11:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We just have to be sure \Nthat we do not let \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.23,0:11:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,anything else get \Nin the way of our attending \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.64,0:12:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,because the meetings are a priority. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.04,0:12:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Hebrews 10:25 says ‘not to forsake’ them.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.64,0:12:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,For everything else\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.64,0:12:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,—reading the Bible, \Npreparing for meetings, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.61,0:12:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,family worship, \Nfield service activity—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.89,0:12:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,we have to set our own schedule \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.25,0:12:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and stick to it as part \Nof a good spiritual routine.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.69,0:12:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,As an example, \Nwhat does your family do \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.30,0:12:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,most Saturday mornings? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.83,0:12:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Many families have the routine \Nof going in field service every Saturday. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.00,0:12:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Rarely is anything allowed \Nto get in the way of that routine. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.04,0:12:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,For them, \NSaturday morning is not the time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.58,0:12:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,for music lessons, \Ndance classes, cooking courses, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.31,0:12:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,working out at the gym, \Nor anything else\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.72,0:12:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—it is their time for field service.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.45,0:12:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Having a routine like that \Nmakes life easier for everyone in the family. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.89,0:12:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,No one has to wonder Friday night \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.23,0:13:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,what is going to happen Saturday morning. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.86,0:13:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The decision has already been made \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.40,0:13:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to go out in the ministry that day. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.24,0:13:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, \Nif we leave it up to chance every week, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.00,0:13:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,then it means \Nthat 52 times during the year \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.24,0:13:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,we have to decide \Nwhether to go in service on Saturday. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.98,0:13:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,How much simpler it is \Nto make the decision once and for all \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.98,0:13:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that we will use \Nthat time slot for the ministry, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.95,0:13:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,barring any serious, \Nunforeseen circumstances. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.02,0:13:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, \Ngiven your family’s situation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.53,0:13:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,another day of the week may work better. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.66,0:13:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But you get the point. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.70,0:13:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Sharing regularly in the Christian ministry \Ncannot be left up to chance. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.13,0:13:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,At Mark 13:10, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.17,0:13:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus prioritized the ministry when he said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.61,0:13:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“The good news has to be preached first.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.91,0:13:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So if spiritual matters are going \Nto take precedence in our lives, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.88,0:13:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,we first have to make them priorities, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.85,0:13:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and second, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.85,0:14:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,make ample time \Nto care for those priorities. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.16,0:14:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That means setting aside \Ndefinite periods of time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.10,0:14:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,to build up our spirituality \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.37,0:14:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and to stay fully involved \Nin our worship and service. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.67,0:14:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Ecclesiastes 3:1 reinforces this thought. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.28,0:14:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It states: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.94,0:14:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“There is an appointed time for everything, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.41,0:14:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,a time for every activity under the heavens.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.12,0:14:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to decide \Nwhen that “appointed time” is \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.52,0:14:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,for each of our spiritual activities. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.62,0:14:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,If we are having difficulty with this, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.19,0:14:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,can we shorten the time \Nwe spend on hobbies, recreation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.13,0:14:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,sports, social networking \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.10,0:14:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and devote that time \Nto our Bible reading, family worship, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.10,0:14:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,meeting preparation, or field ministry? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.14,0:14:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If we can, we will find it \Nto be spiritually refreshing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.38,0:14:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and invigorating.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.98,0:15:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,This was the experience \Nof a family man that I know \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.75,0:15:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,who began preparing better \Nso as to participate each week \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.45,0:15:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,in the “Digging for Spiritual Gems” portion \Nof the midweek meeting. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.06,0:15:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He made time on Sunday evenings for this. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.80,0:15:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,All in his family \Nand congregation have benefited \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.90,0:15:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,from the excellent points he has learned \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.10,0:15:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,as he does research \Non the assigned Bible reading, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.00,0:15:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and he feels good because of it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.27,0:15:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,One married couple decided to eliminate \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.34,0:15:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,some of their hobbies and personal projects. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.08,0:15:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,They even packed them up \Nand put them out of sight. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.68,0:15:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.72,0:15:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So as not to be distracted by those things. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.55,0:15:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They were nonessential activities \Nthat they decided they could do without.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.96,0:15:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Likely, we could all benefit \Nfrom taking inventory of our lives \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.26,0:15:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and limiting any unnecessary activities \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.47,0:15:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that may be interfering \Nwith our spiritual routine. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.64,0:15:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine how rewarding that would be! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.61,0:16:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Just think, if we could buy out \N30 minutes each day \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.14,0:16:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,from doing something \Nthat is not essential, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.65,0:16:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that is about how much time it would take \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.78,0:16:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to read the entire Bible in one year. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.82,0:16:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Or if we could buy out \Nan extra hour or two \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.32,0:16:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,each week for the field ministry, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.36,0:16:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,think of how much more \Nwe could accomplish \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.86,0:16:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and how happy \Nthat would make God and Christ, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.33,0:16:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,as they see us making time \Nfor the more important things!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.27,0:16:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, why have we felt \Nthe need to spend this time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.14,0:16:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,discussing how to manage time? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.98,0:16:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It is because of something else \Nthat the Bible tells us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.95,0:16:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,First Corinthians 7:29 says \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.72,0:16:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that “the time left is reduced.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.45,0:16:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That certainly is true of the time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.45,0:16:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that is left between now \Nand the great tribulation! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.96,0:16:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not the time to neglect \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.76,0:16:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the most important activity of all \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.26,0:16:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—our worship of Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.40,0:16:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Making time for what matters most in life \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.57,0:17:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,is something we all need to do \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.57,0:17:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,—even our young ones. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.57,0:17:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And that’s the focus \Nof this month’s music video \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.24,0:17:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,about the important things.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.13,0:17:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Ev’ry day brings decisions, \Nand we must choose \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.97,0:17:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,How will we spend our time \Nand live for the truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.31,0:17:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, there’s a time to laugh \Nand be with our friends, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.39,0:17:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But it can’t be all \Nwe’re living for in the end. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.99,0:18:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to set time aside \Nfor what’s most important— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.57,0:18:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Prayer, study, \Nand godly devotion. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.27,0:18:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Make Jehovah real, \N’cause that’s really what matters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.11,0:18:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Throw off those things \Npulling us down. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.92,0:18:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about the future \Nand where we are now. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.36,0:18:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let nothing take the place \Nof more important things. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.24,0:18:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Life sure can weigh us down \Nwith bills to pay. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.88,0:18:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It can make us lose sight \Nand misplace our faith. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.12,0:19:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But our fam’ly needs us \Nback at home. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.83,0:19:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we want to be there to help \Nand watch them grow— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.33,0:19:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to set time aside \Nfor what’s most important— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.34,0:19:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Prayer, study, \Nand godly devotion. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.84,0:19:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Make Jehovah real, \N’cause that’s really what matters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.95,0:19:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Throw off those things \Npulling us down. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.69,0:19:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about the future \Nand where we are now. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.99,0:19:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let nothing take the place \Nof more important things. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.85,0:20:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to set time aside \Nfor what’s most important— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.36,0:20:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Prayer, study, \Nand godly devotion. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.16,0:20:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Make Jehovah real, \N’cause that’s really what matters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.54,0:20:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Throw off those things \Npulling us down. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.74,0:20:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about the future \Nand where we are now. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.18,0:20:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let nothing take the place \Nof more important things. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.87,0:20:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What a delightful song, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.04,0:21:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and what precious children \Nwe saw in that music video! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.78,0:21:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, today we invited \Ntwo young people to join us in our studio. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.18,0:21:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Logan, and this is Aiden. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.38,0:21:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for coming.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.55,0:21:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for inviting us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.82,0:21:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you think of that video?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.19,0:21:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I liked it \Nand that it showed a lot of families \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.52,0:21:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,doing stuff that involves Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.33,0:21:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.56,0:21:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The one thing I noticed was \Nthat they were all in a relaxed setting. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.86,0:21:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It was not like in a busy city. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.87,0:21:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,They were at, like, the shore \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.60,0:21:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,where they were talking about the Bible, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.34,0:21:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was nice family time \Nthat they were having.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.04,0:21:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Good observations, Fellas. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.28,0:21:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, three times in the chorus it said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.41,0:21:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,‘We need to set time aside \Nfor the most important things.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.95,0:21:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it mentioned three important things. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.49,0:21:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What were they? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.42,0:21:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Prayer. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.26,0:21:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Study. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.06,0:21:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Godly— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.86,0:21:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,—devotion. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.69,0:21:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s it, very good. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.03,0:21:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Good things for all of us to remember, \Nwouldn’t you say?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.00,0:21:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Well now, my wife and I \Nare in the same congregation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.83,0:21:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,with Logan and Aiden \Nand their families. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.00,0:22:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So I know \Nwhat excellent meeting attenders they are. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.70,0:22:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And what I really appreciate \Nis that you participate in the meetings \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.24,0:22:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and you comment in your own words. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.84,0:22:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s very good and sets a nice example. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.91,0:22:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep it up. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.35,0:22:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Speaking of the meetings, \Nhow do you like the midweek meetings \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.22,0:22:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,with all the videos that we see?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.85,0:22:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It gives a diversity. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.75,0:22:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not always talks. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.92,0:22:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It gives, like, a break in the meeting.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.19,0:22:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.02,0:22:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The videos are always great, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.03,0:22:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and they go with every talk \Nthat the videos are for. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.57,0:22:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And you know, sometimes \Nwe even show Caleb and Sophia videos \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.57,0:22:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,from the Become Jehovah’s Friend series. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.27,0:22:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I’ve got to ask you, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.14,0:22:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have an idea for a new Caleb video?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.18,0:22:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I have one. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.98,0:22:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Caleb is at school; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.62,0:22:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,he gets asked to go \Nto a birthday party at someone’s house. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.38,0:22:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,He goes home and shows his parents the card, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.45,0:22:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and they discuss what he should do about it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.89,0:22:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and then he preaches at school. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.99,0:22:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But before he does that, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.99,0:23:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Sophia gives him a couple of pointers \Non preaching at school and on boldness.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.26,0:23:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.93,0:23:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,How about you Aiden, \Ndo you have an idea?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.97,0:23:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I think a good idea would be: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.24,0:23:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,A new kid comes to Caleb’s class, \Nand it is his birthday, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.21,0:23:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and he passes out the treats. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.68,0:23:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But Caleb says, “No, thank you.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.68,0:23:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he bullies him \Nthat he doesn’t get to have fun; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.95,0:23:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,he doesn’t get treats at school. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.76,0:23:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think \Nhe should discuss it with the family, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.99,0:23:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and then maybe he could tell the boy \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.56,0:23:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,why he doesn’t celebrate birthdays.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.46,0:23:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Very nice. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.57,0:23:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I’m sure the Teaching Committee \Nof the Governing Body \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.93,0:23:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,will give some thought \Nto your recommendations.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.40,0:23:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We brought you to the studio \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.41,0:23:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,because we want you \Nto help me with a little experiment. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.28,0:23:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is an experiment \Nthat some of our viewers have seen before. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.91,0:23:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And you’ve probably seen it, too, \Nbecause it’s mentioned in Volume 2 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.85,0:23:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,of the book Questions Young People Ask\N—Answers That Work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.89,0:24:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And the idea is to help us appreciate \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.49,0:24:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,how we can make time \Nfor “the more important things.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.06,0:24:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let me explain \Nwhat we have on the table. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.06,0:24:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The two pails represent \None week in a Christian’s life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.07,0:24:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The large rocks represent \Nthe most important things \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.74,0:24:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that we need \Nto accomplish during the week, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.90,0:24:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and all these little pebbles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.07,0:24:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,represent the nonessential things of life\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.31,0:24:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,—recreation, playing games, playing sports, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.08,0:24:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,going on the Internet, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.42,0:24:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,working with social media, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.55,0:24:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,our hobbies, taking music lessons. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.05,0:24:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re all fun things to do, \Nbut, really, they’re not essential. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.86,0:24:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, our challenge is \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.86,0:24:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to try to get all the big rocks \Ninto the pail with the little pebbles.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.57,0:24:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So as I hand you each rock, Logan, \NI want you to put it in the pail. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.37,0:24:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this first one represents \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.14,0:24:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the important things \Nthat your father might have to do. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.81,0:24:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He works to support the family. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.21,0:25:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe your mother \Nis a pioneer or has to work secularly. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.25,0:25:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mothers certainly have a lot of work \Nto do around the home caring for the family. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.92,0:25:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And you boys go to school \Nand have homework to do, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.22,0:25:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,so that’s a big part \Nof your time, isn’t it? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.96,0:25:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this rock represents \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.96,0:25:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,all the chores that everyone \Nin the family has to do at home: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.63,0:25:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,cleaning, washing clothes, cooking, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.97,0:25:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,caring for the yard, \Nthe automobile, and so on. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.57,0:25:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That takes a lot of time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.61,0:25:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This rock represents a third of your life\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.15,0:25:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—sleeping. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.42,0:25:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, here are the most important things\N—our spiritual activities. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.86,0:25:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, when we read the Bible \Nand meditate on what we read \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.86,0:25:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and when we do \Npersonal study and family worship. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.00,0:25:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,This one represents \Nall the time it takes for us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.04,0:26:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to prepare for, dress for, travel to, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.54,0:26:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and attend our congregation meetings\N—midweek and on the weekend. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.32,0:26:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And this represents the time we spend \Nin the field service on the weekend. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.92,0:26:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I didn’t tell you \Nthat we can’t go above the top of the pail. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.16,0:26:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,They don’t fit, do they? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.60,0:26:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,No. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.53,0:26:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,OK. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.47,0:26:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And when that happens in a person’s life, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.90,0:26:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,some brothers and sisters \Nare tempted to decide: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.80,0:26:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Well, maybe I’ll skip \Nfield service this week,’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.51,0:26:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,or ‘Maybe I’ll stay home \Nfrom the meetings,’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.01,0:26:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,or ‘Maybe I just won’t get \Nmy Bible reading \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.78,0:26:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and studying and family worship \Ndone this week.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.42,0:26:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But that’s a big mistake, isn’t it? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.42,0:26:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the most important things of life\N—our spiritual activities.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.69,0:26:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So is there some way that we can get \Nall of this into our week’s schedule? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.46,0:26:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Here’s what we’re going to do now. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.66,0:26:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re going to put \Nthe rocks in the empty pail. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.43,0:27:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Logan, \Nsee if you can get them all in there.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.96,0:27:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Very good! They all fit. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.96,0:27:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn’t that nice? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.96,0:27:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We can get the more important things done. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.00,0:27:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But you know, we also want \Na little time for recreation, don’t we? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.43,0:27:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Aiden, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.44,0:27:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s have you pour \Nthe little pebbles into that bucket \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.01,0:27:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and see how much \Nof that you can get in there.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.29,0:27:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You can put a lot more in.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.03,0:28:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Very good! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.07,0:28:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Look how much you got in there! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.07,0:28:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you didn’t get them all in, \Ndid you? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.34,0:28:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But that’s OK because the Bible tells us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.01,0:28:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,we have to ‘buy out the time’ \Nfor the more important things. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.68,0:28:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So, no, we can’t spend all the time \Nthat we may want to on recreation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.88,0:28:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to get \Nthe more important things done.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.22,0:28:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what have we learned \Nfrom this little demonstration? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.12,0:28:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Why weren’t we able to get \Nthe big rocks in the pail the first time? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.26,0:28:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Aiden?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.26,0:28:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there was too much recreation.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.03,0:28:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s right. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.03,0:28:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Logan, why were we able to get \Nall the rocks in the second time?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.17,0:28:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we put in the nonessential things\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.37,0:28:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,—like watching TV, playing video games—\Nin second.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.14,0:28:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We put that in last, didn’t we? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.15,0:28:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.91,0:28:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So that teaches us: \NPut the more important things first. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.22,0:28:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And it all depends \Non what we fill our pail up with, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.99,0:29:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,or our life with, first. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.69,0:29:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much for your help. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.69,0:29:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I appreciate that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.26,0:29:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And keep up your good work \Nas Kingdom publishers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.10,0:29:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and I’ll see you at the Kingdom Hall \Nat the next meeting.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.30,0:29:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,With this illustration in mind—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.04,0:29:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s turn our attention \Nto the Schiller family. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.70,0:29:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it possible to balance raising a family \Nwith a busy spiritual routine? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.64,0:29:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And if circumstances allow, \Ncan parents reach out for spiritual goals \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.11,0:29:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,—even full-time service? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.25,0:29:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s listen to their answers \Nto those questions.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.74,0:29:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes people say: \N“Well, you know, what was your secret? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.26,0:29:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,How did you raise six kids?”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.49,0:29:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We got married September 16, 1972. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.40,0:29:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Two things started coming quickly \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.63,0:29:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,—spiritual privileges came along \Nand the children came along— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.80,0:29:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,together. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.24,0:29:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I was made an elder \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.81,0:29:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,shortly after the elder arrangement \Ncame into effect.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.51,0:30:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The kids were just part of all that, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.68,0:30:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and you might think \Nthat sometimes they didn’t know it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.29,0:30:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We were doing \Nsubstitute work with five children, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.46,0:30:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and I don’t think they \Neven knew what we were doing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.73,0:30:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1989, we were pioneering, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.60,0:30:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we had the opportunity \Nto help out at Bethel, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.43,0:30:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe a week or two at a time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.04,0:30:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,About that time, \NPatterson was starting up. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.24,0:30:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And we kind of recognized \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.61,0:30:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that maybe we were getting too comfortable.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.12,0:30:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We went one time to Bethel and said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.72,0:30:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“Hey, if you need a doctor out at Patterson, \Nwhy, we’d be available. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.76,0:30:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Or we could make ourselves available, \Nmaybe.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.19,0:30:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And wouldn’t you know it, \Nshortly after, we got a call, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.76,0:30:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“How quickly could you \Nsell your place and be up here?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.27,0:30:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So we went to Bethel with six kids, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.84,0:30:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,sold our house at a loss so we could do that, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.27,0:31:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and started a new life there.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.81,0:31:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So we learned pretty quickly: \NDon’t turn down any privileges \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.05,0:31:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,—and especially not because we had kids. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.95,0:31:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When we went to Bethel, \Nthe oldest one was 17. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.42,0:31:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Having children \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.43,0:31:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,kept my husband and me very humble \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.10,0:31:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,because as soon as you thought \Nyou had something figured out, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.40,0:31:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,each child needed \Nto be disciplined in a different way. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.70,0:31:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And as soon as you thought, \N‘Boy, you know, I’ve got this figured out,’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.21,0:31:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you’re thrown a curve. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.47,0:31:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,A challenge was \Nto keep doing the basic things. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.61,0:31:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You’d come home tired. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.55,0:31:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be so easy \Nnot to have the family study \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.69,0:31:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe one Monday. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.89,0:31:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s those basic, simple things \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.53,0:31:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that I think kept us on an even keel.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.83,0:31:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I often think \Nof the illustration that Jesus gave \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.63,0:32:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,at the end of the Sermon on the Mount, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.64,0:32:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,what he said about this foundation \Nthat was washed away. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.27,0:32:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jesus never blamed the storm; \Nhe blamed the foundation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.61,0:32:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we recognize that any child anywhere \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.32,0:32:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,—in fact, even adults— \Ncan get their faith tested. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.02,0:32:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So we tried to really make sure \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.02,0:32:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,they had a good foundation \Nthat didn’t get washed away.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.06,0:32:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare them, \Nlet them learn how to deal with people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.76,0:32:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,while they’re under your care, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.03,0:32:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and get them ready for life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.93,0:32:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We got to thinking, ‘Other parents \Nrequire their kids to go to college,’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.40,0:32:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,so we just required them \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.31,0:32:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to pioneer for a year. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.64,0:32:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Any kind of education— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.98,0:32:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Any kind of secular education can teach you \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.25,0:32:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,how to have a skill so that you have a job. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.72,0:32:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But the Bible teaches you how to live, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.72,0:32:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and it teaches you principles \Nthat you can live your life by. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.93,0:33:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And all of them kept pioneering. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.43,0:33:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, they did various jobs \Nto support themselves. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.73,0:33:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,They cleaned; they worked at lumberyards; \Nthey worked on roofing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.10,0:33:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And none of them have \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.27,0:33:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,a complicated life that holds them down.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.78,0:33:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted everlasting life \Nfor my children, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.34,0:33:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and I knew I would have to give \Nthem back to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.75,0:33:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to realize we don’t own our children\N—Jehovah does. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.22,0:33:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And we have to respect that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.22,0:33:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re not telling them what to do anymore. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.39,0:33:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We appreciate \Nand we’re very, very thankful \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.73,0:33:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,when our children, \Nas far away as they are \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.36,0:33:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and as busy as they are, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.36,0:33:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,take the time to communicate with us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.24,0:33:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And I know you won’t remember this, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.94,0:33:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,but I remember one time, \Nbefore you fell asleep at night, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.98,0:33:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, \N“With all that you have done for Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.78,0:33:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,what would you like in return?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.52,0:34:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember what you said? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.49,0:34:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You said three words, “All my children.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.89,0:34:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,In Deuteronomy it says: \N“I have put life and death before you, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.23,0:34:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . and you must choose.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.27,0:34:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can do what we can as parents \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.40,0:34:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,—some things good, \Nsome things not so good. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.27,0:34:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, each one had to make \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.37,0:34:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,his or her own decision. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.98,0:34:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And that’s why, again, \Nit was not any secret we had. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.65,0:34:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re so proud of what the kids decided \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.55,0:34:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and how they turned out \Nbecause it was their decision. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.96,0:34:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that’s the thing that we’ve learned: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.89,0:34:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t turn down opportunities.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.67,0:34:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn’t it wonderful to hear of ones \Nlike Brother and Sister Schiller \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.37,0:34:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,who have offered their gifts to Jehovah? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.21,0:34:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Schiller said \Nthat it was doing the basic things \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.31,0:34:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that kept his family focused spiritually. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.05,0:35:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So when opportunities came along, \Nhe was able to do more, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.92,0:35:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,which included pioneering, \Nsubstitute circuit work, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.49,0:35:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and using the medical training \Nhe had already acquired \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.59,0:35:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,to volunteer \Nat the Patterson Educational Center. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.33,0:35:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Proverbs 10:22 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.66,0:35:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“It is the blessing of Jehovah \Nthat makes one rich, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.47,0:35:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and He adds no hardship with it.”(Ftn.) \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.30,0:35:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That certainly has proved true \Nfor Brother Schiller and his family. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.54,0:35:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We can all agree that one of the ways \NJehovah provides spiritual riches \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.38,0:35:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is through the training \Nwe receive at meetings, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.98,0:35:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,assemblies, conventions, \Nand even special schools. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.99,0:35:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Such training helps us to prioritize \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.09,0:35:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and to do “the more important things.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.59,0:35:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Over the past few years, \Nmembers of the Bethel family \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.36,0:35:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,have attended the Pioneer Service School. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.86,0:35:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s see how the school has helped them \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.13,0:35:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in their Bethel service \Nand in their ministry.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.74,0:36:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a really great privilege \Nfor us as Bethelites \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.38,0:36:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,to be able to study for six days. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.85,0:36:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The Governing Body \Ngiving us time to study more\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.72,0:36:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,about Jehovah’s qualities was tremendous \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.42,0:36:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to help build our spirituality.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.52,0:36:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,For many Bethelites, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.53,0:36:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,this was like a gift from Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.19,0:36:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,because they had never attended before. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.36,0:36:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, one couple \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.60,0:36:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,who had been 50 years in full-time service \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.30,0:36:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,had never attended the pioneer school before.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.64,0:36:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d been invited twice before, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.81,0:36:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,but unfortunately, \Nboth times I wasn’t able to go. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.21,0:36:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt like Jehovah \Nwas giving me a third chance, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.51,0:36:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and this time I wouldn’t miss it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.82,0:36:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,At first, you feel a little like, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.32,0:36:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,this is strange; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.39,0:36:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you’re at Bethel; \Nyou’re not out pioneering. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.39,0:36:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, \Nwhen you’ve gone to the school \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.63,0:36:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and you’ve seen what the school \Nactually does for your ministry, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.13,0:36:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,it was really— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.23,0:36:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see why the Governing Body— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.57,0:37:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It was such a kind gift for them \Nto give us this privilege of coming.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.40,0:37:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re surrounded by people \Nwho have been pioneers for years; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.21,0:37:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,some have been to Gilead; \Nsome have been in the traveling work; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.41,0:37:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,some have conducted \Npioneer schools themselves. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.85,0:37:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s the best.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.05,0:37:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though they’re \Nin this spiritual environment, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.99,0:37:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,they need to be upbuilt.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.25,0:37:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,As Bethelites, \Nwe go out in service \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.96,0:37:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,not as much as we did \Nwhen we were pioneering. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.59,0:37:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So being able to have \Nan effective use of our time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.56,0:37:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in the ministry makes a big difference.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.00,0:37:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You learn a lot about the field ministry \Nin pioneer school. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.77,0:37:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So in a month when 30 hours was an option, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.64,0:37:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I applied to auxiliary pioneer \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.97,0:37:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and I also tried to participate \Na lot in the ministry on weekends. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.31,0:37:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This way I was able \Nto prepare for the school.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.05,0:37:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that every Christian \Nneeds to have goals, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.25,0:37:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and even for us serving in Bethel, \Nwe need goals. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.02,0:37:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So the main thing I learned from the school \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.19,0:37:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,is that even while working in Bethel, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.16,0:37:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I can do more for the congregation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.09,0:38:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and make a bigger effort in the ministry.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.03,0:38:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,After the pioneer school, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.86,0:38:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized I needed to cultivate \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.50,0:38:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,more humility in my Bethel service \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.84,0:38:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and the field ministry.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.44,0:38:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there’s so much spiritual food \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.34,0:38:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,available at Bethel, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.28,0:38:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,it can become easy to neglect personal study. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.71,0:38:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Listening to the deeply meditated comments \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.32,0:38:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,from the students \Nand the instructors really stimulated me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.89,0:38:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to also meditate more deeply.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.29,0:38:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,During the school, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.89,0:38:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to study more than usual, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.23,0:38:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,so I had to set aside more time for reading \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.46,0:38:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,so as to be well-prepared for class.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.13,0:38:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It was really practical for me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.10,0:38:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to improve my ministry, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.13,0:38:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was really nice \Nbecause with this new school, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.07,0:38:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,we had a demonstration \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.57,0:38:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of what we have to avoid \Nand what is good to do.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.24,0:38:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a demonstration \Nabout what not to do on a Bible study, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.95,0:38:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and I saw myself doing some of those things. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.88,0:38:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So I realized that I really needed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.15,0:38:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to get better at conducting Bible studies.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.69,0:39:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember one demonstration that taught us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.06,0:39:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,how we can witness informally \Nin a supermarket line, for example. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.03,0:39:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That demonstration \Ngave me more confidence \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.20,0:39:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to witness informally.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.07,0:39:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,In the school,\Nwe learned a lot about Jesus\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.10,0:39:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,—how he was hardworking, zealous, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.81,0:39:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and showed genuine interest \Nin the people around him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.88,0:39:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That example helped me \Nto be more hardworking and zealous, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.65,0:39:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as to be more approachable \Nto those whom I work with.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.25,0:39:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s why we’re here in Bethel\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.28,0:39:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,—it’s to support the preaching work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.55,0:39:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So it doesn’t matter what assignment we have. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.95,0:39:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,In a way, it’s connected to that.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.32,0:39:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The fruitage of the spirit \Nis good not just for the ministry \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.93,0:39:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but it’s good for everything in everyday life \Ntoward our brothers and sisters.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.76,0:39:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Love is such an important quality \Nfor Bethelites. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.14,0:39:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I work in the Computer Department, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.94,0:39:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,but I don’t treat computers with love. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.07,0:39:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But the school strengthened my determination \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.44,0:39:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to treat my brothers and sisters with love.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.11,0:40:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of all the other schools I’ve attended, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.15,0:40:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,this school had the most impact on my life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.42,0:40:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,In just one week, \Nit strengthens our faith, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.22,0:40:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,widens our view of things, \Ntrains our conscience, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.22,0:40:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and deepens our love.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.36,0:40:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It definitely \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.26,0:40:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,stimulated the pioneer spirit. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.53,0:40:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though we’re not pioneers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.26,0:40:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,it helped us to understand \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.53,0:40:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the importance of the pioneer service \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.27,0:40:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and how it contributes \Nto our overall joy \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.04,0:40:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,in serving Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.51,0:40:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So that’s something \Nthat we would never want to neglect. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.31,0:40:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We really appreciated \Nthe emphasis that was placed on that \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.65,0:40:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and how it also helps to keep \Nour close relationship with Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.35,0:40:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly, we can see \Nthe blessings that have come \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.06,0:40:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,from making time \Nfor that additional spiritual training. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.89,0:40:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual training at Bethel \Nalso includes morning worship. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.07,0:40:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Many of you have expressed appreciation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.53,0:40:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,for the morning worship programs \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.54,0:40:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,posted on JW Broadcasting. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.14,0:41:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s listen to Brother Geoffrey Jackson \Nof the Governing Body \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.64,0:41:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,as he shows us how we \Ncan maintain a faithful life course \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.68,0:41:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,like that of Abraham.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.48,0:41:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,This morning I’d like you to imagine \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.65,0:41:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,for a few moments \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.65,0:41:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that you’ve been asked to write \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.69,0:41:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,your life story for The Watchtower. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.39,0:41:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, once you get over the shock, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.59,0:41:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,how would you go about doing that? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.00,0:41:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ve probably noticed with many \Nof the life experiences in The Watchtower, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.60,0:41:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,usually the first paragraph, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.94,0:41:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,have a defining moment in that person’s life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.37,0:41:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, Brother Eric Beveridge, \Nwho serves with us here in the United States, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.28,0:41:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,he started off this way: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.51,0:41:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘I hereby sentence you \Nto six months in prison.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.15,0:41:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“With those words ringing in my ears, \NI was taken off to . . . \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.59,0:41:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“[p]rison in Manchester, England. . . . \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.59,0:41:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“I had just faced \None of the toughest tests of my young life \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.56,0:41:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,—I had refused to be conscripted \Nfor military service.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.40,0:41:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Or another brother, Brother Harley Harris, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.73,0:42:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,who served as a missionary \Nin Ecuador for many years, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.67,0:42:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,he referred to the date September 2, 1950. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.51,0:42:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He said: “We were at a circuit assembly, \Nsurrounded by a mob. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.31,0:42:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“The mayor brought in the National Guard \Nto protect us from the unruly crowd. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.78,0:42:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“Soldiers with drawn rifles \Nand bayonets lined the street. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.75,0:42:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“Amid insults, \Nwe walked to our cars and drove to . . . \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.46,0:42:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,“the remaining sessions of the assembly. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.62,0:42:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It was there \Nthat I was baptized at the age of 14.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.03,0:42:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Or another brother, Brother Don MacLean \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.10,0:42:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,—who serves \Non the Branch Committee in Australasia, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.70,0:42:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,a brother originally from Canada— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.00,0:42:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,made this comment. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.00,0:42:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He started his life experience: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.21,0:42:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“There I sat, hour after hour, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.54,0:42:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“with one of the Royal Canadian \NMounted Police by my side. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.75,0:42:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“I was his prisoner. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.75,0:42:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,“We were headed \Nfor the prison camp at . . . Ontario, Canada, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.12,0:42:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“and it seemed \N[that] the 1,500-mile train trip \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.69,0:42:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,would never end.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.52,0:42:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, those certainly were defining moments \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.83,0:43:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,in the lives of those brothers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.86,0:43:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What about you? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.86,0:43:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What is your defining moment? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.10,0:43:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you might be thinking, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.37,0:43:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,‘No one put a gun \Nto my head and said, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.84,0:43:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“Decide now whether \Nyou’ll serve Jehovah or not.”’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.18,0:43:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But for many of us, there have been \Ndefining moments in our lives. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.68,0:43:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps it’s the moment \Nyou decided to serve Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.18,0:43:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,or the moment you decided \Nto become a full-time servant. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.39,0:43:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps it involved some decisions, \Nsuch as selling a home, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.73,0:43:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,selling a business, \Ndeciding to move to Bethel, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.50,0:43:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,or perhaps leaving your country \Nand going somewhere else. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.53,0:43:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Or it may have involved \Ncertain tests or trials, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.44,0:43:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps giving up \Nopportunities for education \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.64,0:43:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,or for lucrative job opportunities. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.18,0:43:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, whatever the case, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.25,0:43:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sure most of us \Nhave had some defining moments \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.15,0:43:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,in our lives that we remember \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.15,0:44:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,—the decisions that were made \Nthat resulted in much good.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.16,0:44:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s think for a moment \Nabout the faithful man Abraham. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.13,0:44:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the defining moment in his life? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.20,0:44:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if you take your Bibles \Nand turn with me to Hebrews chapter 11, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.40,0:44:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,of course, here we see \Nthe apostle Paul giving us an outline \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.41,0:44:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,or history of many \Nof the defining moments \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.38,0:44:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,in the lives of faithful ones. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.08,0:44:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,At Hebrews 11:8, \Nit says of Abraham: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.48,0:44:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,“By faith Abraham, when he was called, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.02,0:44:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“obeyed by going out to a place \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.69,0:44:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“he was to receive as an inheritance; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.63,0:44:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,he went out, \Nalthough not knowing where he was going.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.10,0:44:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that was a defining moment \Nin the life of Abraham, wasn’t it? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.80,0:44:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,He decided to obey Jehovah, \Nto leave Ur, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.81,0:44:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and to travel to a distant country \Nthat he didn’t really know about. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.15,0:45:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But was that all that was involved \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.32,0:45:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,with Abraham receiving the reward? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.39,0:45:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,No. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.39,0:45:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read on a little further in verse 9. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.16,0:45:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,There it says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.43,0:45:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“By faith he lived as a foreigner \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.93,0:45:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“in the land of the promise \Nas in a foreign land, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.93,0:45:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“living in tents with Isaac and Jacob, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.37,0:45:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,the heirs with him \Nof the very same promise.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.37,0:45:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this is not a defining moment, is it? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.54,0:45:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a course of faithfulness, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.11,0:45:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,day in, day out. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.05,0:45:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what’s the point? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.08,0:45:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in the case of Abraham, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.09,0:45:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,we remember \Nthat eventually he and his family \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.66,0:45:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,crossed the Euphrates River \Nand into the Promised Land \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.66,0:45:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,in the year 1943 B.C.E. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.83,0:45:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But he had to wait 25 years \Nbefore his son Isaac was born \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.60,0:45:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and then another 60 years \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.27,0:45:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,before his grandsons \NEsau and Jacob were born. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.54,0:46:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And eventually, \Nhe died after being in the Promised Land \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.08,0:46:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,as a foreigner for about 100 years.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.85,0:46:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what’s the point? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.85,0:46:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Although there was \Na definite decision he made \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.25,0:46:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,—a defining moment in his life—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.92,0:46:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that was backed up as verse 9 says, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.02,0:46:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,by his faithfulness \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.19,0:46:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,—day in, day out—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.70,0:46:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,serving Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.80,0:46:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So the lesson we learn from that is \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.87,0:46:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that it’s not just the defining moments \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.24,0:46:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that define who we are. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.61,0:46:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather, those moments and those decisions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.41,0:46:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,need to be backed up by faithful service. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.81,0:46:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s be quite frank. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.05,0:46:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Many of the life experiences \Nthat we read in The Watchtower \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.65,0:46:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,may have a very exciting first paragraph. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.96,0:46:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,“Yes, they put a gun to my head. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.09,0:46:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,“Make your decision. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.29,0:46:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“Will you die? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.76,0:46:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you be willing to die for Jehovah?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.20,0:46:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, \Nwhen you read the rest of the article, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.13,0:47:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing really exciting \Nhappened in that person’s life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.84,0:47:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sorry to say it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.37,0:47:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That includes my life experience as well. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.04,0:47:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.48,0:47:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the majority of our lives \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.38,0:47:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,are not involved with defining moments \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.65,0:47:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,—exciting things that are happening. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.02,0:47:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather, they involve \Nour faithfulness to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.39,0:47:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can’t just rely \Nupon these defining moments and say, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.56,0:47:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,“Well, I made this decision \Nto serve Jehovah; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.20,0:47:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I passed this test, \Nso everything is good.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.70,0:47:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we need to continue \Nto back up those defining moments \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.71,0:47:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,with faithful service. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.01,0:47:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember that in the Scriptures, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.04,0:47:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,there were many who had \Ndefining moments in their lives. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.15,0:47:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Take, for example, Solomon. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.32,0:47:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He had a defining moment, didn’t he, \Nwhen he prayed to Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.15,0:47:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and he was praised for the fact \Nthat he asked for wisdom rather than wealth? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.93,0:48:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But that wasn’t backed up by faithfulness. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.30,0:48:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, that defining moment in his life \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.33,0:48:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,really wasn’t as valuable as it could’ve been \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.63,0:48:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,because of his lack of faithfulness.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.80,0:48:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And what about Judas Iscariot? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.34,0:48:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Were there some defining moments in his life? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.68,0:48:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously, he decided \Nto follow Jesus at one point. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.51,0:48:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And during that time, \Nwhen he faithfully followed Jesus, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.72,0:48:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,no doubt, there were very exciting, \Ninteresting things that happened. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.39,0:48:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But again, \Nthose defining moments in his life \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.73,0:48:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,proved to be of little value \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.73,0:48:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the lack \Nof faithfulness on his part. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.43,0:48:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So that helps us to understand \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.63,0:48:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,why the apostle Paul \Nsaid some very interesting points \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.10,0:48:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,just before he started this list \Nthat he gives us in Hebrews chapter 11. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.78,0:48:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s turn to Hebrews chapter 10, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.55,0:48:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Hebrews 10:35-39. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.95,0:49:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice, this is the point \Nthat we should gain from this lesson. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.96,0:49:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul says starting in verse 35: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.26,0:49:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“Therefore, do not throw away your boldness, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.63,0:49:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“which will be richly rewarded. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.64,0:49:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,For you need endurance,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.07,0:49:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,now, that reminds us of what Jesus said \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.71,0:49:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,about ‘the one who endures \Nto the end will be saved,’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.21,0:49:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“so that after you \Nhave done the will of God, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.31,0:49:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“you may receive \Nthe fulfillment of the promise. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.65,0:49:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,“For yet ‘a very little while,’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.89,0:49:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“and ‘the one who is coming \Nwill arrive and will not delay.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.72,0:49:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘But my righteous one \Nwill live by reason of faith,’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.23,0:49:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,“and ‘if he shrinks back, \NI have no pleasure in him.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.90,0:49:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“Now we are not the sort \Nwho shrink back to destruction, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.74,0:49:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,but the sort who have faith \Nfor the preserving of our lives.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.74,0:49:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What a very positive comment that is. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.74,0:50:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we think of our life experience, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.65,0:50:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,don’t be disappointed if you \Ndon’t have some spectacular things \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.75,0:50:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that you can mention as defining moments. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.39,0:50:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, the important thing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.22,0:50:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is not just the decisions \Nthat we make along the way \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.00,0:50:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,but the fact that we remain \Nfaithful to Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.43,0:50:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,day in, day out. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.54,0:50:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,As Brother Jackson mentioned, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.54,0:50:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,we might experience \Na “defining moment” in our spiritual lives, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.37,0:50:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,but real faithfulness is shown \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.44,0:50:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,in how we handle \Nsmaller challenges day to day. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.18,0:50:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,One example might be if someone \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.18,0:50:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,were to attack \Nour beliefs in front of others. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.92,0:50:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever experienced that? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.92,0:50:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Were you nervous? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.76,0:50:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you find it challenging to find \Nthe right words to make a defense? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.86,0:50:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,In the next video, \Nnotice how the character of Grayson \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.33,0:50:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,deals with a similar situation.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.73,0:51:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It was one of those mornings \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.01,0:51:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,when everything seemed to be going right. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.44,0:51:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, this whole year was going right \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.19,0:51:15.41,Default,,0,0,0,,ever since I got baptized. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.41,0:51:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,My family is closer than ever. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.86,0:51:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve made some good friends \Nin the congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.66,0:51:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I even started a Bible study. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.07,0:51:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It felt good to let go of my fears \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.84,0:51:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and serve Jehovah with everything I have. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.30,0:51:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But things can change very quickly.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.94,0:51:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, I’m sorry. \NYou know what? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.44,0:51:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I saw Grayson \Nover the weekend on Saturday. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.15,0:51:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I think he might be one of those people \Nthat tells you about the Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.36,0:51:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,One of those, uh—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.95,0:51:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re saying Grayson is a Jehovah’s Witness?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.20,0:52:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. \NLet me go ask him.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.74,0:52:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Grayson?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.78,0:52:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, how’s it going, Ron?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.83,0:52:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I see you on Saturday morning \Nover on Main Street?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.62,0:52:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. \NYou know, I’m one of Jehovah’s Witnesses. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.17,0:52:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And what we do, \Nwe go out and talk to people about—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.38,0:52:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sorry. \NI just don’t get it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.84,0:52:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll go knocking on strangers’ doors \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.76,0:52:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to support your own religion, \Nyet you won’t stand and support this country. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.30,0:52:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don’t you people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.81,0:52:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,get involved and make \Na real difference for once?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.69,0:52:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I was really disappointed in myself. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.27,0:52:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess I hadn’t moved past \Nall my fears like I thought. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.62,0:52:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Later that night, \Nfor family worship, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.83,0:52:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,we sat down and discussed \Nour brothers who were in prison \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.71,0:52:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,for their faith.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.50,0:52:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, why are they in prison?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.17,0:52:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They don’t want to fight; \Nthey don’t want to kill people.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.01,0:52:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It really touched Aiden. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.43,0:53:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He was moved to pray for them that night. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.43,0:53:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,His prayer touched my heart. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.93,0:53:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And with so much on my mind, \NI couldn’t sleep. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.68,0:53:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So I decided to get up \Nand do some research. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.86,0:53:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I found some information \Non the apostle Peter. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.36,0:53:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite his zeal, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.11,0:53:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,he also struggled at times \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.20,0:53:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,with fear of man \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.38,0:53:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,like when he denied Jesus three times. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.33,0:53:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But eventually, he overcame that fear.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.29,0:53:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We strictly ordered you \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.09,0:53:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,not to keep teaching \Non the basis of this name, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.32,0:53:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet look! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.76,0:53:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you have filled Jerusalem with your teaching, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.80,0:53:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and you are determined \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.89,0:53:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to bring the blood of this man upon us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.10,0:53:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We must obey God as ruler rather than men. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.72,0:53:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The God of our forefathers raised up Jesus, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.48,0:53:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,whom you killed, \Nhanging him on a stake.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.54,0:54:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,“Always ready to make a defense \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.38,0:54:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“before everyone who demands of you a reason\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.43,0:54:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,for the hope you have”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.81,0:54:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,—Peter focused on his hope, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.85,0:54:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,not his fear. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.14,0:54:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like these faithful brothers \Nhave been doing, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.94,0:54:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to be like them \Nand make Jehovah proud of me.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.08,0:54:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The next day I woke up, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.08,0:54:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was thinking about the apostle Peter \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.71,0:54:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and our brothers \Nwho were in prison for their faith. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.59,0:55:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And even though I was still a little nervous, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.68,0:55:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt ready to talk to Eric.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.73,0:55:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ron, Eric. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.73,0:55:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry I didn’t get a chance \Nto explain the other day, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.98,0:55:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,but if you have a moment now, \NI’d love to be able to talk to you.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.14,0:55:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t want to hear it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.11,0:55:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Grayson.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.32,0:55:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought that was it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.54,0:55:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But it wasn’t. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.33,0:55:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron said he wanted to know more. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.66,0:55:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I’ll never completely \Nget rid of my fears. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.80,0:55:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But my love for Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.59,0:55:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and the example of his courageous servants \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.26,0:55:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,helps me to be ready to meet the challenge.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.76,0:55:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The other day I wanted to show you something.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.73,0:55:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What a practical example \Nof how taking time to meditate \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.54,0:56:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,on Biblical or modern integrity-keepers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.34,0:56:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,can help us have \Nthe courage to defend our faith! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.74,0:56:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just another example \Nof how making time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.08,0:56:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,for “the more important things”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.08,0:56:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,—such as prayer, study, and godly devotion—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.65,0:56:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,can help us remain faithful. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.69,0:56:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Before we conclude our program, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.89,0:56:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s take a moment \Nand travel to the country of Hungary. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.96,0:56:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Situated in the center of Europe, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.07,0:56:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,visitors to Hungary \Ncan enjoy delicious food and wine \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.67,0:56:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and see the beautiful great plain \Nknown as the Puszta. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.34,0:56:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Water also plays a vital role \Nthroughout the country, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.68,0:56:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,with its abundant rivers, \Nlakes, and thermal springs. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.71,0:56:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There are more than 21,000 publishers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.72,0:56:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and close to 300 congregations. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.45,0:56:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re offering waters of truth to others, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.95,0:56:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,often in spite of severe economic challenges. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.39,0:56:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, during the last ten years, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.59,0:56:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the number of regular pioneers \Nhas nearly doubled.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.06,0:57:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,In 2016, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.07,0:57:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,a pregroup \Nin the Lovari language was formed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.60,0:57:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,This language is spoken \Nby many Roma people in Hungary. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.67,0:57:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,While none in the group \Nis a native Lovari speaker, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.58,0:57:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,they’re willing to learn this language \Nto help these thirsty ones. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.75,0:57:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Additionally, this year, \Nnearly 30,000 foreign students \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.09,0:57:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,enrolled at various universities \Nin Hungary, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.09,0:57:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,providing a very diverse territory \Nfor those serving \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.43,0:57:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,in a foreign-language congregation \Nor group. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.10,0:57:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Our brothers and sisters from Hungary \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.83,0:57:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,are overjoyed to send \Ntheir love and greetings to all of you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.60,0:57:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We send them our Christian love in return.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.51,0:57:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,From the world headquarters \Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.35,0:57:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,this is JW Broadcasting.\N
